            <biogHist>
                <p>Alexander Macbain was born on 22 July 1855, the illegitimate son of  John Macbain
                    and Margaret Mackintosh. Despite growing up in poverty, he went on to become an
                    eminent Celtic scholar, and part of a group of intellectuals including Alexander
                    Carmichael. His most important work was the <span localType="mods-titleinfo"
                        >Gaelic Etymological Dictionary</span>, published in 1896.</p>
